tomcat restart

sh /opt/tomcat/bin/shutdown.sh
sh /opt/tomcat/bin/startup.sh


You need to go this path via root /opt/tomcat and run the below command:
sh bin/startup.sh >>>> for restaring the tomcat service

use ubic command for ea tomcat applications.
for example: /home/sarakuapp/ea-tomcat85/bin

(For tomact with cpal ubic is configured.)

https://docs.cpanel.net/knowledge-base/web-services/the-cpuser_service_manager-script-and-the-ubic-subsystem/


also can be in root/tomcat/bin

do sh bin/startup.sh >>>> for restaring the tomcat service


